Data Dictionary

2022-09-01

Source: vignettes/data_dictionary.Rmd
data_dictionary.Rmd

Vocabulary

Accident

An event that has occurred that could not have been reasonably foreseen or prevented. 27/10/2022

Amenity

The ability of people to make use of something for reasons that may not be economic 27/10/2022

Category

A classification of the significance of an event used to make decisions about SEPA's response and for recording purposes NA

Complainant

A person making a complaint. 27/10/2022

Complaint

Information passed to SEPA that the complainant believes should require action 12/10/2022

Environmental event

An incident that leads to a negative impact on the environment 12/10/2022

Event ID

A URN for an individual event 12/10/2022

Evidence

Could be physical, e.g. samples, or information like a witness statement. Material that demonstrates something has happened and/or an identified person or persons are responsible. 27/10/2022

Flooding Event

Water covering land it doesn't normally cover. 12/10/2022

Harm

An assessment of the degree of negative environmental impact 12/10/2022

Impact

The degree by which circumstances have deviated from normal 12/10/2022

Incident

Something occuring that has led to or has the potential to lead to an event. 12/10/2022

Location

A geographic label to say where something has taken place. 27/10/2022

Major event

An event that requires multi-agency response, where SEPA may not be the lead agency. 27/10/2022

Measurement

Length, area, concentration, temperature, weight, volume, speed etc. 12/10/2022

Media

The type of environment experiencing the impact 27/10/2022

Notification

Information being transmitted to SEPA that needs to be recorded / indicates SEPA needs to take action 12/10/2022

Notifier

Somebody or something transmitting information to SEPA 27/10/2022

Observation

Making a specific qualitative assessment. 12/10/2022

Operator

The entity undertaking an activity that has given rise to an event 27/10/2022

Pathway

The route by which an event reaches a receptor from source 27/10/2022

Receptor

The thing that gets impacted by an event 27/10/2022

Report

A narrative explanation of what happened and why, and actions taken 27/10/2022

Sample

A piece of physical evidence gathered 27/10/2022

Site

A place where activities are taking place that have caused an event 27/10/2022

Source

The point at which the event originated. The source for the contamination / the origin of the waste 27/10/2022

Substantiation

The act of verifying an event has occurred NA

Time notified

Date and time SEPA receives a notification of an event having been taken place 27/10/2022

Time observed

Date and time evidence of an event is observed 27/10/2022

Time of measurement

Date and time of making a quantitative assessment 27/10/2022

Time of occurence

Date and time the event took place 27/10/2022

Time of sampling

Date and time of gathering physical evidence 27/10/2022

Title

A short name describing the event so everyone knows which one they are talking about 12/10/2022
